To obtain a clear knowledge of other persons it is therefore necessary to start with a right notion of self. This notion is obtained from the feelings which are awakened in us by our physical perceptions, as has already been described, and forms a standard of measurement. And to form a just estimate of our- selves it is necessary to know others: we thus obtain a standard of comparison.
